Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium buff-brown; red inclusions. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Astymedes. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria Museum ALEX ABC 001.01.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0735)
